reviews.reviewText: These are the best tissues on the market. I was pleasantly surprised at how much better they are than Puffs or Kleenex, which I always buy. These are thicker, as soft, and there are more per box. I’m placing another order now.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good product at a great price
reviews.reviewText: I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of these tissues at this price point. They are about as thick and just as soft as the basic kind of name brand tissues we used to use. The Kleenex extra soft tissues and Puffs Plus tissues are a bit softer, so I may still buy those if one of us gets a cold, but for daily use, these Presto tissues work great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better value than Costco’s Kirkland Tissues
reviews.reviewText: I wanted to compare these tissues to Costco’s Kirkland tissues. These were just as nice and sturdy and soft as the Kirkland brand. In fact, i think they are nicer and softer. I also appreciate that the first one comes out of the box by itself. With Kirkland, you get two right away. Also, they all come out without a gap, meaning sometimes in the Kirkland brand, you'll pull out a tissue and then the rest are left inside the box with none ready to pull out. Never have this problem with the Amazon brand. Only issue is the single slit in the plastic for the tissues to come out of. The single slit makes pulling them out a bit harder. So I simply used a scissors and cut two cross slits in the plastic. That helped a lot.The reason I wanted to compare is because you can get 18 boxes of the Amazon brand for roughly the same price as the Kirkland 12 pack. I will be switching to this product. I don’t have to drive to Costco to get tissues anymore.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Rough compared to PUFFS.
reviews.reviewText: Puffs used to be sooooo good. Not so much these days the quality has gone down hill. However Kleenex has improved some of it's branched out competition lines to compete with Puffs. I went with these to try out a new tissue box I bought and only had the full size Puff boxes on hand. Well maybe a mistake. However I will use them up over the winter and just not buy again. I live 200 miles round trip to the world of shopping like Wally world and Target etc. I know there are still rural places in the USA here in MT that are that far away from ultra populations. I think the term is fly over zone. Most of the USA is fly over. Love Amazon gives us options to stay in touch and enjoy what others enjoy. However this one let me down. On the good note it didn't fall apart when using. It's kind of stiff not super soft but works fine in a pinch just not for if I got a cold and needed tissues all day long. It would ruin my nose for sure then. So if you are an occasional sniffer this may be for you but I've got sinus problems and need a little more reliable and soft approach 24/7. My fault for buying actually so not a 1 star...I'd give it a 3 for trying.
